-- United Rentals sees higher EPS in 2008 on lower total sales
-- 
-- Thu Jan 10, 2008 5:25pm EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/01/10/us-unitedrentals-outlook-idUSWNAS622220080110

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - United Rentals Inc ( URI.N ) said on Thursday it expects to earn $2.80 to $3.00 a share in 2008, up from $2.55 to $2.60 a share in 2007. 

 The company, the world's largest equipment rental company, said it expects to report rental revenue of $2.71 billion in 2008, up from an expected $2.63 billion in 2007. But it said its sees total revenue -- which includes trench safety operations, contractor supplies and used equipment sales -- slipping to $3.53 billion in 2008, down from an expected $3.73 billion in 2007.